    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Artifact Promotion Gates Across Environments"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Build promotion is the discipline of moving "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "the same immutable artifact",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " through a sequence of environments \u2014 dev, staging, production \u2014 where each transition requires passing a defined gate. For Claude applications, these gates include not just infrastructure checks but also eval pass rates, prompt version hashes, and security probe results encoded into a deployment manifest."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Promote artifacts, not code. The same container image that passed CI should be the exact image deployed to production \u2014 no rebuilds, no 'it works on my machine'."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This sub-subtopic covers how to structure the three-gate promotion model, what the deployment manifest must contain, how gates are enforced in automation, and how to handle rollbacks when a gate fails post-deploy."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Artifact promotion gates across dev, staging, and production environments",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Immutable Artifact Principle"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The foundation of build promotion is that the artifact created by CI is never rebuilt. The same Docker image SHA, prompt version, and model configuration that survived CI gates is the exact artifact deployed to every subsequent environment."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "No environment-specific builds:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Environment configuration (API endpoints, feature flags) is injected at runtime via environment variables, not baked into the image."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Content-addressed references:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Refer to artifacts by their SHA digest ("
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "image@sha256:abc123",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "), not by a mutable tag like "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "latest",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Prompt version in the manifest:",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The prompt hash is recorded at build time. Deploying a different prompt requires a new build, which means re-running all CI gates."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Deployment Manifest"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every successful CI build produces a deployment manifest \u2014 a signed JSON document that records everything needed to reproduce or audit the deployment. This manifest travels with the artifact through every promotion gate."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/generate_manifest.py\n\"\"\"Generate and sign the deployment manifest after a successful CI run.\"\"\"\nimport json, hashlib, datetime, os, pathlib\nfrom prompts import prompt_hash\n\ndef generate_manifest(\n    image_digest: str,          # from: docker inspect --format '{{index .RepoDigests 0}}'\n    build_sha: str,             # from: git rev-parse HEAD\n    eval_pass_rate: float,\n    probes_passed: int,\n    probes_total: int,\n    model: str,\n    prompt_name: str = \"customer_support\",\n    env: str = \"production\",\n) -> dict:\n    manifest = {\n        \"schema_version\": \"1.0\",\n        \"build_sha\": build_sha,\n        \"build_timestamp\": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \"Z\",\n        \"image_digest\": image_digest,\n        \"model\": model,\n        \"prompt_name\": prompt_name,\n        \"prompt_hash\": prompt_hash(prompt_name, env=\"production\"),\n        \"eval_pass_rate\": round(eval_pass_rate, 4),\n        \"eval_threshold\": 0.85,\n        \"security_probes_passed\": probes_passed,\n        \"security_probes_total\": probes_total,\n        \"gates_passed\": eval_pass_rate >= 0.85 and probes_passed == probes_total,\n    }\n    # Content hash for tamper detection (sign with KMS in production)\n    content = json.dumps(manifest, sort_keys=True, separators=(\",\", \":\"))\n    manifest[\"manifest_hash\"] = hashlib.sha256(content.encode()).hexdigest()\n    return manifest\n\ndef save_manifest(manifest: dict, out_path: str = \"manifest.json\"):\n    pathlib.Path(out_path).write_text(json.dumps(manifest, indent=2))\n    print(f\"Manifest written: {out_path}\")\n    print(f\"  image:       {manifest['image_digest']}\")\n    print(f\"  prompt_hash: {manifest['prompt_hash']}\")\n    print(f\"  eval rate:   {manifest['eval_pass_rate']:.1%}\")\n    print(f\"  probes:      {manifest['security_probes_passed']}/{manifest['security_probes_total']}\")\n    print(f\"  gates_passed:{manifest['gates_passed']}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Gate 1: CI All-Pass (Build \u2192 Dev)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Every commit that passes all CI jobs (lint, unit, contract, eval, security) is automatically promoted to the dev environment. No manual approval is needed at this gate \u2014 dev is the lowest-risk environment and the fastest feedback loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/promote-to-dev.yml\nname: Promote to Dev\non:\n  workflow_run:\n    workflows: [CI]\n    types: [completed]\n    branches: [main]\n\njobs:\n  promote-dev:\n    if: ${{ github.event.workflow_run.conclusion == 'success' }}\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Download manifest from CI\n        uses: actions/download-artifact@v4\n        with:\n          name: deployment-manifest\n          run-id: ${{ github.event.workflow_run.id }}\n          github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n\n      - name: Verify manifest gates passed\n        run: |\n          python3 -c \"\n          import json, sys\n          m = json.load(open('manifest.json'))\n          if not m['gates_passed']:\n              print('Manifest gates_passed=False \u2014 refusing promotion')\n              sys.exit(1)\n          print(f'Promoting {m[\"image_digest\"][:20]}... to dev')\n          \"\n\n      - name: Deploy to dev\n        env:\n          KUBECONFIG: ${{ secrets.DEV_KUBECONFIG }}\n        run: |\n          IMAGE=$(jq -r .image_digest manifest.json)\n          kubectl set image deployment/claude-app app=$IMAGE -n dev\n          kubectl rollout status deployment/claude-app -n dev --timeout=120s\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Gate 2: Smoke Evals and Contract Tests (Dev \u2192 Staging)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "After deploying to dev, a smaller smoke eval suite runs against the live dev endpoint. This catches integration-level issues (the app correctly passes the prompt to Claude, tool calls are routed correctly) that unit tests cannot detect."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/promote-to-staging.yml\nname: Promote to Staging\non:\n  workflow_run:\n    workflows: [Promote to Dev]\n    types: [completed]\n\njobs:\n  gate-2-smoke:\n    if: ${{ github.event.workflow_run.conclusion == 'success' }}\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Run smoke evals against dev\n        env:\n          APP_URL: ${{ secrets.DEV_APP_URL }}\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: |\n          pytest tests/evals/smoke/             --app-url=$APP_URL             --eval-threshold=0.90 \\   # higher threshold for smoke subset\n            --tb=short\n\n      - name: Run contract tests against dev API\n        env:\n          APP_URL: ${{ secrets.DEV_APP_URL }}\n        run: pytest tests/contract/ --app-url=$APP_URL --tb=short\n\n  promote-staging:\n    needs: [gate-2-smoke]\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - name: Deploy to staging\n        env:\n          KUBECONFIG: ${{ secrets.STAGING_KUBECONFIG }}\n        run: |\n          IMAGE=$(jq -r .image_digest manifest.json)\n          kubectl set image deployment/claude-app app=$IMAGE -n staging\n          kubectl rollout status deployment/claude-app -n staging --timeout=180s\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Gate 3: Full Validation and Manual Approval (Staging \u2192 Production)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The staging gate is the most comprehensive. After a successful staging deploy, the full eval suite, E2E tests, load test, and security probe replay all run against staging. Only then is a manual approval requested for production promotion."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "yaml"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# .github/workflows/promote-to-prod.yml\nname: Promote to Production\non:\n  workflow_run:\n    workflows: [Promote to Staging]\n    types: [completed]\n\njobs:\n  gate-3-full-validation:\n    if: ${{ github.event.workflow_run.conclusion == 'success' }}\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      - name: Full eval suite against staging\n        env:\n          APP_URL: ${{ secrets.STAGING_APP_URL }}\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: pytest tests/evals/ --eval-threshold=0.85 --tb=short\n\n      - name: E2E + load test against staging\n        env:\n          STAGING_APP_URL: ${{ secrets.STAGING_APP_URL }}\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: pytest tests/e2e/ --tb=short\n\n      - name: Security probe replay against staging\n        env:\n          STAGING_APP_URL: ${{ secrets.STAGING_APP_URL }}\n          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}\n        run: pytest tests/red_team/test_probe_replay.py --tb=short\n\n  request-manual-approval:\n    needs: [gate-3-full-validation]\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment:\n      name: production    # GitHub environment with required reviewers\n    steps:\n      - name: Approved \u2014 promote to production canary\n        env:\n          KUBECONFIG: ${{ secrets.PROD_KUBECONFIG }}\n        run: |\n          IMAGE=$(jq -r .image_digest manifest.json)\n          # Deploy as canary: 10% traffic initially\n          kubectl set image deployment/claude-app-canary app=$IMAGE -n prod\n          kubectl rollout status deployment/claude-app-canary -n prod --timeout=300s\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Configuring the GitHub Environment for Manual Approval"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The production environment in GitHub requires at least one named reviewer to approve before the job runs. Create this in the repository settings under Environments \u2192 production \u2192 Required reviewers."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Gate Metrics in the Manifest"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each gate appends its results to the manifest before promoting, creating an audit trail of exactly what passed at each stage:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# scripts/update_manifest.py\n\"\"\"Append gate results to the manifest during promotion.\"\"\"\nimport json, pathlib, datetime\n\ndef append_gate_result(\n    manifest_path: str,\n    gate_name: str,             # e.g. \"gate_2_smoke_evals\"\n    passed: bool,\n    details: dict,\n):\n    manifest = json.loads(pathlib.Path(manifest_path).read_text())\n    if \"gate_results\" not in manifest:\n        manifest[\"gate_results\"] = []\n    manifest[\"gate_results\"].append({\n        \"gate\": gate_name,\n        \"passed\": passed,\n        \"timestamp\": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat() + \"Z\",\n        **details,\n    })\n    pathlib.Path(manifest_path).write_text(json.dumps(manifest, indent=2))\n\n# Usage in CI:\n# append_gate_result(\n#     \"manifest.json\",\n#     \"gate_2_smoke_evals\",\n#     passed=True,\n#     details={\"pass_rate\": 0.96, \"cases_run\": 25},\n# )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
